This paper discusses the requirements for education in Computer Science . First, a description of the core curriculum is given . This core curriculum is based on author's experience i n teaching of Computer Science at the under graduate and graduate levels . The specific areas of education in Computer Scienc e in which hands on experience is ver y essential are described . The instructional tools which are available, as well a s those which may be easily designed fo r hands on experience are described an d discussed in terms of cost, ease o f maintenance, modificability and support facilities . Specific examples are provided through case studies .